許多分析師說，杨荣文仍是行動黨黨員的當兒（憲法禁止總統持有任何黨籍），他的聲望似乎勝於他在阿裕尼集選區的敗選。一些分析師稱，若楊決定參選，基於他擔任了數個內閣職務，<ref>{{cite news|last=Ye|first=Weiqiang|title=觀察家：競逐總統大選　楊榮文比陳清木更受國人歡迎 (Translation: Analysts: In Presidential Race, George Yeo Seems to be More Popular than Tan Cheng Bock)|url=http://news.omy.sg/News/Local%2BNews/Story/OMYStory201106021533-249785.html|accessdate=2011-06-07|newspaper=[[Shin_Min_Daily_News|Shin Min Daily News]]|date=2011-06-02|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110610163836/http://news.omy.sg/News/Local%2BNews/Story/OMYStory201106021533-249785.html|archivedate=2011-06-10}}</ref>應該非常適合參選總統。其他分析師批評楊宣佈日後不再競選失去的國會議席的速度，他聲稱性格不適合擔任總統，以及在競逐的選舉中和行動黨劃清界限的難度的可能性。<ref name="news.omy.sg"/><ref>[http://news.asiaone.com/News/AsiaOne%2BNews/Singapore/Story/A1Story20110601-281943.html George Yeo may consider running for President] {{Wayback|url=http://news.asiaone.com/News/AsiaOne%2BNews/Singapore/Story/A1Story20110601-281943.html |date=20110604150210 }}, news.asiaone.com, 1 June 2011</ref>

楊拒絕參選總統之後，政治分析師稱陳慶炎是比較適合的人選之一，即使陳慶炎當時還未宣佈競選。<ref>{{cite news|last=Wong|first=Tessa|title=Tony Tan seen as likely candidate|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/BreakingNews/Singapore/Story/STIStory_680816.html|accessdate=2011-06-17|newspaper=[[Straits_Times|Straits Times]]|date=2011-06-17|author2=Elgin Toh|author3=Andrea Ong|archive-date=2011-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111125093244/http://www.straitstimes.com/BreakingNews/Singapore/Story/STIStory_680816.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==政經界反應==

自從六月底，[[新加坡律政部|律政部]]長[[尚穆根|尚穆根]]表示關切選民及准候選人混淆或錯誤解讀總統的權利，澄清總統的能與不能。<ref>{{cite news|last=Guo|first=Lijuan|title=律政部長發表聲明：獲授權治理國家的是總理　民選總統有監管權無行政權 (Translation: Minister for Law Issues Statement: The Person Authorised to Run the Country is the Prime Minister. The President has Supervisory Powers, and No Executive Powers)|url=http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201106110400-251641.html|accessdate=2011-06-22|newspaper=[[Lianhe_Zaobao|Lianhe Zaobao]]|date=2011-06-11|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110624031616/http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201106110400-251641.html|archivedate=2011-06-24}}</ref>八月份，他在一個論壇說：“總統只能對內閣授權的議題發言”，而且“履行職責必須按照內閣建議。”他也說：“如果（總統）是一個給予總理少許或者不給予尊重的人，那麼勢力當然會有限。”<ref>{{cite news|title=President can only speak and act as advised by the Cabinet|url=http://news.asiaone.com/News/AsiaOne%2BNews/Singapore/Story/A1Story20110806-293038.html|accessdate=2011-08-21|newspaper=Asiaone|date=2011-08-06|archive-date=2011-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111019200357/http://news.asiaone.com/News/AsiaOne%2BNews/Singapore/Story/A1Story20110806-293038.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Ramesh|first=S|title=PE: Presidency must be handled with judicious care: Shanmugam|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/singaporelocalnews/view/1145264/1/.html|accessdate=2011-08-21|newspaper=Channel News Asia|date=2011-08-05|archive-date=2012-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023101815/http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/singaporelocalnews/view/1145264/1/.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 當時的六位有意願參選的總統候選人對於他對總統職責的說明。<ref>{{cite news|title=Presidential hopefuls react to Shanmugam remarks|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/BreakingNews/Singapore/Story/STIStory_699610.html|accessdate=2011-08-21|newspaper=The Straits Times|date=7 August  2011|archive-date=2011-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110814042259/http://www.straitstimes.com/BreakingNews/Singapore/Story/STIStory_699610.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

七月初，在一封寫給華文報《[[聯合早報|聯合早報]]》的電郵中，[[李顯龍|李顯龍]]總理表揚陳慶炎在內閣時的表現，給予陳慶炎絕對支持，說陳慶炎若當選總統，必能團結全民並為國增光。<ref>{{cite news|last=Zhou|first=Shuyin|title=李總理：陳慶炎若當選總統　必能團結全民並為國增光 (Translation: PM Lee: Should Tony Tan Be Elected, He Will Be Able to Unite the People, and Bring Honor to the Country.)|url=http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201106260401-255083.html|accessdate=2011-07-04|newspaper=[[Lianhe_Zaobao|Lianhe Zaobao]]|date=2011-06-26|author2=Huang Huimin|language=zh-hans|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008223017/http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201106260401-255083.html|archivedate=2011-10-08}}</ref>

八月初，[[新加坡国家发展部|國家發展部]]長[[许文远|许文远]]呼應了李顯龍在[[三巴旺|三巴旺]]的國慶宴會上對於陳慶炎的意見，聲稱他會是一位很優秀的總統，為國爭光。許盡所有的力量支持陳慶炎，公開希望陳慶炎能勝選。<ref>{{cite news|last=Li|first=Yuanyi|title=許文遠相信陳慶炎會是一位很優秀的總統 (Translation: Khaw Boon Wan Believes Tony Tan Will Be An Excellent President)|url=http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201108070427-265783.html|accessdate=2011-08-08|newspaper=[[Lianhe_Zaobao|Lianhe Zaobao]]|date=2011-08-07|language=zh-hans|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008223458/http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201108070427-265783.html|archivedate=2011-10-08}}</ref>

在告別過去的當兒，{{tsl|en|National Trades Union Congress|全國職工總會}}（職總）會長和國會議員[[林瑞生|林瑞生]]說，职总不会强迫職總各工會支持一位候选人，他们想支持誰就支持誰。<ref>{{cite news|last=Cai|first=Xinying|title=林瑞生：職總各工會或支持不同總統候選人 (Translation: Lim Swee Say: NTUC's Constituent Trades Union May Back Different Candidates)|url=http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201108050423-265439.html|accessdate=2011-08-08|newspaper=[[Lianhe_Zaobao|Lianhe Zaobao]]|date=2011-08-05|language=zh-hans|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008223645/http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201108050423-265439.html|archivedate=2011-10-08}}</ref>

==竞选==

大规模的竞选活动，直至七月末才出现。6月17日报道了第一例的竞选。《[[新明日報|新明日报]]》报道，陈清木已开始访全国各巴刹见选民。<ref>{{cite news|last=Zheng|first=Kaiwen|title=政治觀察家：陳慶炎比楊榮文更適合當總統 (Political Analysts: Tony Tan is More Suitable for the Presidency than George Yeo)|url=http://news.omy.sg/News/Local%2BNews/Story/OMYStory201106171521-253243.html|accessdate=2011-06-17|newspaper=[[Shin_Min_Daily_News|Shin Min Daily News]]|date=2011-06-17|language=zh-hans|quote=陳清木已開始訪巴剎見選民 (Tan Cheng Bock has already started meeting with voters at bazaars)|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110620015336/http://news.omy.sg/News/Local%2BNews/Story/OMYStory201106171521-253243.html|archivedate=2011-06-20}}</ref>

8月1日，《新明日报》报道，四位准总统候选人于周末见选民。陈钦亮到[[印度尼西亚|印度尼西亚]][[巴淡岛|巴淡岛]]见区内的新加坡选民，陈清木则在本地的青年公园会见年轻选民。<ref>{{cite news|last=Ye|first=Weiqiang|title=准總統參選人　4陳週末頻曝光 (Translation: The 4 "Tans" Presidential Hopeful Were Frequently Seen over the Weekend)|url=http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201108011512-264273.html|accessdate=2011-08-03|newspaper=[[Shin_Min_Daily_News|Shin Min Daily News]]|date=2011-08-01|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008223204/http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201108011512-264273.html|archivedate=2011-10-08}}</ref>

8月7日，《[[联合早报|联合早报]]》报道，陈清木已走访全岛十个邻里，也打算走访更多的邻里。<ref>{{cite news|last=Huang|first=Weiman|title=陳清木已走訪全島10個鄰里 (Translation: Tan Cheng Bock Has Visited 10 Neighbourhoods on the Island)|url=http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201108070427-265784.html|accessdate=2011-08-08|newspaper=[[Lianhe_Zaobao|Lianhe Zaobao]]|date=2011-08-07|language=zh-hans|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008223757/http://news.omy.sg/News/Presidential%2BElection/Story/OMYStory201108070427-265784.html|archivedate=2011-10-08}}</ref>

新加坡所有选举都有开支限制。一名总统候选人不可花超过[[新加坡元|新币]]60万元，或是每名选民3角钱，两者数额都不可超过。超过开支限制，将罚款2000元，外加三年内取消在任何选举参选或投票的资格。<ref>{{cite web|title=ELECTION EXPENSES LIMIT|url=http://www.elections.gov.sg/candidates_expenseslimit.html|publisher=Singapore Elections Department|accessdate=2011-06-07|archive-date=2011-05-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110530152112/http://www.elections.gov.sg/candidates_expenseslimit.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

7月8日，[[李显龙|李显龙]]总理發佈总统竞选的声明。总理说，由于电视覆盖范围极大，总统选举的竞选活动大多是在电视上。每名候选人将以总统候选人广播的方式获得10分钟的免费广播时间，而这些广播将被翻译。第一次将在17日提名日播出，第二次将在投票日前夕播出。此外，[[新传媒私人有限公司|新传媒]]会制作一系列候选人的节目。<ref>{{cite web|title=Campaigning for the Presidential Election|url=http://www.elections.gov.sg/pressrelease/PreE2011/Statement%20from%20PMO.pdf|publisher=Prime Minister's Office, Singapore|accessdate=2011-08-08|archive-date=2011-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809194432/http://www.elections.gov.sg/pressrelease/PreE2011/Statement%20from%20PMO.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==投票==
新加坡政府在8月3日宣佈，把投票日定於8月27日。<ref name=electiondateset/>

預計有227萬選民在選舉中投票，但是實際投票數是215萬。當局宣佈，選民將在“印有總統候選人照片以及候選人選擇的图形標誌的選票”上投下神聖的一票。這是讓新加坡選民在選票上能更輕易辨認總統候選人。

有史以來第一次，選民如果沒有收到郵寄來的投票卡，即可到選舉局網站打印投票卡。<ref>{{cite web|title=PE: S'poreans to start receiving poll cards for PE|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/singaporelocalnews/view/1147674/1/.html|publisher=Channel News Asia|accessdate=2011-08-22|archive-date=2012-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120716192804/http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/singaporelocalnews/view/1147674/1/.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

有14萬國人由於2011年大選中沒有投票而從選民名單上去除，而有7萬1000人已恢復選民資格。<ref name="ooi2" />

在新加坡，投票是強制性的。凡是從名字選民名單去除的選民，在將來的總統選舉或大選沒有投票資格，也無法在選舉中參選。選民可到選民註冊局恢復選民資格，若沒有合理的理由，將罰款50元。<ref name=needtovote>{{cite web|title=Voting is Compulsory|url=http://www.elections.gov.sg/voters_compulsory.html|publisher=Singapore Elections Department|accessdate=2011-06-07|archive-date=2011-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110612165807/http://www.elections.gov.sg/voters_compulsory.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==选举结果==

晚上8时，投票站关闭，接着投票箱被密封，送到计票中心。本地时间晚上10时30分，投票结束的两小时半后，陈钦亮是第一个承认败选的候选人。他补充说，他可能拿不回4万8000元选举按金，不过竞选经验很有用。陈钦亮说，他有几分失望，但是他深信他打了个很好的仗，预料可以做得更好。他暗示选举结果，说“前两名候选人之间将是一场艰苦的战斗”。被问及是哪前两名候选人，陈拒绝置评。<ref>{{cite news | title = PE:Presidential candidate Tan Kin Lian concedes defeat | publisher = Channel NewsAsia | date = 2011-08-27 | url = http://pe.channelnewsasia.com/stories/elections2/view/1082139/1/PE-Presidential-candidate-Tan-Kin-Lian-concedes-defeat }}{{dead link|date=2017年11月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref>

8月28日凌晨1时19分，选举局宣布，由于领先的两名候选人，陈庆炎和陈清木的选票有少于2%之差，将会重新计算选票。声明说，第一次总计有少于百分之二之差后，选举官“允许重新计算所有选票”。<ref>{{cite news | title = PE: Elections Dept allows recount of votes | publisher = Channel NewsAsia | date = 2011-08-28 | url = http://pe.channelnewsasia.com/stories/elections2/view/1082144/1/PE-Elections-Dept-allows-recount-of-votes }}{{dead link|date=2017年11月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref>

新加坡时间凌晨4时23分，位于布连拾街的选举局，选举官{{tsl|en|Yam Ah Mee|杨雅镁}}公布选举结果。<ref name="Channel NewsAsia">{{cite news | title = PE: Dr Tony Tan elected Singapore's 7th President | publisher = Channel NewsAsia | date = 2011-08-28 | url = http://pe.channelnewsasia.com/stories/elections2/view/1082146/1/PE-Dr-Tony-Tan-elected-Singapores-7th-President }}{{dead link|date=2017年11月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref>

